<p>although of course they spoke French quite fluently &amp; asked me many questions about Australia &amp; Australians during our little journey of 3 kilom&egrave;tres.<br/> Before leaving my "friends in need", I managed to surprise them with the few words of Italian I have picked up. At Beaumont I only stayed a few minutes &amp; after having to undergo the ordeal of embracing the whole family &amp; receiving all sorts of good wishes, etc. etc. took  my departure.<br/>Wednes. 28" June<br/>Today the loading of the equipment &amp; stores on to the train has been commenced. It is raining steadily [indecipherable] at 7 a.m. so that matters are not improved by the "dew from heaven" &ndash; a lot of our stuff such as blankets &amp; clothing being done up in bales.</p>
